        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>When shopping for an engagement ring or a special diamond ring, you’ll often come across two popular styles: side stone rings and halo rings. At first glance they may seem similar because both include additional diamonds around the center stone. But once you look closely, you’ll notice that they create very different visual effects.</p><p>Some people prefer the balanced look of side stones along the band, while others love the bright frame of diamonds that a halo creates around the center stone. Both styles can make a ring look more brilliant, but they achieve that sparkle in different ways.</p><p>At <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Lucira Jewelry\">Lucira Jewelry</a>, you’ll find beautiful examples of both styles. Rings such as the Oval Cut with Side Diamonds Accent Engagement Ring highlight the center diamond with delicate side stones, while designs like the Round Halo Split Diamond Ring use a halo to create a dramatic, radiant look.</p><p>Understanding how these two ring styles differ can make it easier to choose the one that fits your taste.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qTUdW8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "What a Side Stone Ring Looks Like and How It Enhances the Center Diamond",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>What a Side Stone Ring Looks Like and How It Enhances the Center Diamond</h2>",
            "custom_id": "what-a",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_dqaPLA": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>A <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/side-stone-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"side stone ring\">side stone ring</a> features smaller diamonds placed along the band, usually on either side of the center stone. These stones act as supporting accents that help draw attention to the main diamond.</p><p>The center diamond remains the main focus, while the side stones add a bit more sparkle and balance to the design.</p><p>A good example is the Oval Cut with Side Diamonds Accent Engagement Ring from Lucira. The smaller diamonds on the band naturally guide the eye toward the oval center diamond, making it stand out without overwhelming the ring.</p><p>Side stone rings often feel elegant and balanced. They offer extra brilliance while still maintaining a clean and classic look.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
