        "rich_text_9LDfB8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Which Style Should You Choose?",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Which Style Should You Choose?</h2>",
            "custom_id": "which-style",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_gDLUXU": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The best choice really depends on your personal taste.</p><p>If you prefer a classic and understated ring, side stones might be the better option. They add sparkle but still keep the design simple.</p><p>If you want maximum brilliance and a bold look, a halo ring could be the right fit. The surrounding diamonds make the center stone stand out dramatically.</p><p>Some people even choose rings that combine both elements, such as a halo with additional accent stones on the band.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_RMT8Xk": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Lucira Approach to Diamond Ring Design",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Lucira Approach to Diamond Ring Design</h2><p>At<a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\" Lucira Jewelry\"> Lucira Jewelry</a>, both side stone and halo designs are crafted with careful attention to balance. The goal is always to highlight the center diamond while creating a ring that feels comfortable and elegant.</p><p>Lucira rings feature IGI-certified lab-grown diamonds, offering exceptional brilliance while supporting responsible sourcing.</p><p>Whether you prefer the refined elegance of side stones or the radiant glow of a halo setting, Lucira designs rings that celebrate the beauty of diamonds in different ways.</p>",
            "custom_id": "the-lucira",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        }
      },
